## General Testing Best Practices:
- Implement proper test isolation with beforeEach/afterEach hooks
- Use meaningful test descriptions that explain business requirements
- Structure tests in arranged-act-assert pattern
- Implement custom test reporters for clearer failure messages
- Set explicit timeouts for async operations rather than arbitrary waits

## Pitfalls to Avoid:
- Don't test permissions with admin accounts that bypass restrictions
- Avoid hardcoding permission checks in tests that might change in production
- Don't skip negative permission tests (verify forbidden actions fail correctly)
- Don't use production database for permission tests
- Don't test only the happy path - include validation errors
